# ClientPilot AI — Core Context

## What it is
Multi-tenant SaaS. WhatsApp AI receptionist for aesthetic clinics, dental practices, and SMBs.
Each **business** has one WhatsApp number (Twilio or Meta Cloud API). Inbound messages run through
an AI pipeline (Claude) that classifies intent, builds a context-aware reply, and handles
appointment booking via Google Calendar.

## Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 15 App Router, React 19, TypeScript strict
- **Database**: Supabase (Postgres + Auth + RLS). Types generated via `pnpm run db:types`.
- **AI**: Anthropic Claude (`ANTHROPIC_MODEL` env, default `claude-sonnet-4-5`)
- **Messaging**: Twilio WhatsApp (primary) + Meta Cloud API (secondary, `meta_phone_number_id`)
- **Queues**: BullMQ + IORedis. Three queues: `followups`, `reminders`, `reviews`
- **Worker**: `workers/index.ts` — run separately with `pnpm run worker`
- **Payments**: Stripe (plans: `starter` / `pro` / `clinic`)
- **Email**: Resend
- **Calendar**: Google Calendar OAuth (tokens encrypted at rest with `TOKEN_ENCRYPTION_KEY`)

## Module map
| Concern | Location |
|---|---|
| Domain types | `lib/types.ts` |
| Env validation | `lib/env.ts` (also exports `PLAN_LIMITS`) |
| AI pipeline | `lib/ai/pipeline.ts` → intent → prompt → respond |
| Supabase server | `lib/supabase/server.ts` (anon+cookie) |
| Supabase admin | `lib/supabase/admin.ts` (service-role, bypasses RLS) |
| Queue definitions | `lib/queue.ts` |
| Worker entrypoint | `workers/index.ts` |
| Webhooks | `app/api/twilio/webhook/`, `app/api/meta/webhook/`, `app/api/stripe/webhook/` |
| Calendar | `lib/calendar/booking.ts`, `lib/calendar/google.ts` |
| WhatsApp senders | `lib/twilio.ts`, `lib/whatsapp/meta.ts` |
| Auth middleware | `middleware.ts` → `lib/supabase/middleware.ts` |
| Migrations | `supabase/migrations/` |

## Multi-tenancy rule
Every business-scoped table has `business_id`. **Always filter by `business_id` explicitly**
when using the admin client (it bypasses RLS). The server client enforces RLS automatically.

## Plans
`starter`: 500 AI responses/month | `pro`: 2 000 | `clinic`: unlimited
Counter: `businesses.ai_responses_this_month`. Resets on `invoice.paid` Stripe event.
